Events.text: The Italian city of Castro is completely destroyed by the forces of Pope Innocent X, ending the Wars of Castro.

Events.text: The Great Fire of London breaks out and burns for three days, destroying 10,000 buildings including St Paul's Cathedral.

Events.text: Great Britain adopts the Gregorian calendar, nearly two centuries later than most of Western Europe.

Events.text: During what became known as the September Massacres of the French Revolution, rampaging mobs slaughter three Roman Catholic Church bishops, more than two hundred priests, and prisoners believed to be royalist sympathizers.
Events.html: During what became known as the September Massacres of the French Revolution, rampaging mobs slaughter three Roman Catholic Church bishops, more than two hundred priests, and prisoners believed to be royalist sympathizers.

Events.text: A massive landslide destroys the town of Goldau, Switzerland, killing 457.
Events.html: A massive landslide destroys the town of Goldau, Switzerland, killing 457.

Events.text: The Royal Navy bombards Copenhagen with fire bombs and phosphorus rockets to prevent Denmark from surrendering its fleet to Napoleon.
Events.html: The Royal Navy bombards Copenhagen with fire bombs and phosphorus rockets to prevent Denmark from surrendering its fleet to Napoleon.

Events.text: The University of Oslo is founded as The Royal Fredericks University, after Frederick VI of Denmark and Norway.
Events.html: The University of Oslo is founded as The Royal Fredericks University, after Frederick VI of Denmark and Norway.

Events.text: Oberlin College is founded by John Jay Shipherd and Philo P. Stewart in Oberlin, Ohio.
Events.html: Oberlin College is founded by John Jay Shipherd and Philo P. Stewart in Oberlin, Ohio.

Events.text: The Tianjing incident takes place in Nanjing, China.
Events.html: The Tianjing incident takes place in Nanjing, China.

Events.text: American Civil War: United States President Abraham Lincoln reluctantly restores Union General George B. McClellan to full command after General John Pope's disastrous defeat at the Second Battle of Bull Run.
Events.html: American Civil War: United States President Abraham Lincoln reluctantly restores Union General George B. McClellan to full command after General John Pope's disastrous defeat at the Second Battle of Bull Run.

Events.text: American Civil War: Union forces enter Atlanta, a day after the Confederate defenders flee the city, ending the Atlanta Campaign.
Events.html: American Civil War: Union forces enter Atlanta, a day after the Confederate defenders flee the city, ending the Atlanta Campaign.

Events.text: Mutsuhito, Emperor Meiji of Japan, marries Masako Ichijō. The Empress consort is thereafter known as Lady Haruko.
Events.html: Mutsuhito, Emperor Meiji of Japan, marries Masako Ichijō. The Empress consort is thereafter known as Lady Haruko.

Events.text: Franco-Prussian War: Battle of Sedan: Prussian forces take Napoleon III of France and 100,000 of his soldiers prisoner.
Events.html: Franco-Prussian War: Battle of Sedan: Prussian forces take Napoleon III of France and 100,000 of his soldiers prisoner.

Events.text: Rock Springs massacre: In Rock Springs, Wyoming, 150 white miners, who are struggling to unionize so they could strike for better wages and work conditions, attack their Chinese fellow workers killing 28, wounding 15 and forcing several hundred more out of town.

Events.text: Battle of Omdurman: British and Egyptian troops defeat Sudanese tribesmen and establish British dominance in Sudan.
Events.html: Battle of Omdurman: British and Egyptian troops defeat Sudanese tribesmen and establish British dominance in Sudan.
